52.8	History_of_virtual_learning_environments	History of virtual learning environments	A virtual learning environment (VLE) is a system that creates an environment designed to facilitate teachers in the management of educational courses for their students, especially a system using computer hardware and software, which involves distance learning. In North America, a virtual learning environment is often referred to as a "learning management system" (LMS).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/5c/Pressey_Testing_Machine_1.jpg/150px-Pressey_Testing_Machine_1.jpg
